# 🎯 YouTube Focus Mode

A free, open-source browser extension that blocks YouTube Shorts and
recommendations so you only watch what you actually came to watch.

Built with plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
No tracking. No ads. No accounts. Just focus.

> 📦 **Repository:** https://github.com/rejoelbhutia/Browser_focus_extension

---

## ✨ What It Does

| Toggle | What gets hidden |
|---|---|
| **Block Shorts** | Shorts cards on home, search results, and the Shorts nav link |
| **Hide Sidebar** | The "Up Next" recommendations panel on video watch pages |
| **Clean Home Page** | The infinite video grid on youtube.com |
| **Remove End Cards** | Clickable video overlays at the end of videos |

Settings are saved locally and persist after closing the browser.

---

## 🚀 Installation

### Step 1 — Clone the repository

Open your terminal and run:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/rejoelbhutia/Browser_focus_extension.git
```

This downloads the extension into a folder called `Browser_focus_extension`.
That folder is the extension — you load it directly into your browser below.

> Don't have Git? Click the green **"Code"** button on the
> [GitHub page](https://github.com/rejoelbhutia/Browser_focus_extension)
> and select **"Download ZIP"**, then unzip it.

---

### Step 2 — Load into your browser

---

#### 🦁 Brave

1. Go to `brave://extensions`
2. Enable **Developer mode** (toggle, top-right)
3. Click **Load unpacked**
4. Select the `Browser_focus_extension` folder
5. ✅ Done — click the extension icon in the toolbar to toggle features

---

#### 🌐 Chrome

1. Go to `chrome://extensions`
2. Enable **Developer mode** (toggle, top-right)
3. Click **Load unpacked**
4. Select the `Browser_focus_extension` folder
5. ✅ Done — click the extension icon in the toolbar to toggle features

---

#### 🌐 Microsoft Edge

1. Go to `edge://extensions`
2. Enable **Developer mode** (toggle, left sidebar)
3. Click **Load unpacked**
4. Select the `Browser_focus_extension` folder
5. ✅ Done — click the extension icon in the toolbar to toggle features

---

#### 🧭 Opera

1. Go to `opera://extensions`
2. Enable **Developer mode** (toggle, top-right)
3. Click **Load unpacked**
4. Select the `Browser_focus_extension` folder
5. ✅ Done — click the extension icon in the toolbar to toggle features

---

#### 🦊 Firefox

**Temporary install** (resets when Firefox closes):

1. Go to `about:debugging#/runtime/this-firefox`
2. Click **Load Temporary Add-on...**
3. Open the `Browser_focus_extension` folder and select `manifest.json`
4. ✅ Done

**Permanent install:**

Firefox requires extensions to be signed by Mozilla to persist.

1. Zip the `Browser_focus_extension` folder
2. Create a free account at [addons.mozilla.org](https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/developers/)
3. Go to **Submit a New Add-on → On your own**
4. Upload the zip — Mozilla signs it and gives you a `.xpi` file
5. Drag and drop the `.xpi` into Firefox to install permanently

---

#### 🍎 Safari (macOS)

**Requirement:** Xcode (free from the Mac App Store)

1. Open Terminal and run:
   ```bash
   xcrun safari-web-extension-converter /path/to/Browser_focus_extension
   ```
2. Xcode opens automatically — click **Run (▶)**
3. In Safari go to **Settings → Extensions** and enable **YouTube Focus Mode**

> If you don't see the Extensions tab:
> Safari → Settings → Advanced → check **"Show Develop menu"**
> Then: Develop menu → **Allow Unsigned Extensions**

---

#### 📱 Firefox for Android

1. Install [Firefox for Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=org.mozilla.firefox)
2. Type `about:debugging` in the address bar
3. Tap **Load Temporary Add-on**
4. Select `manifest.json` from the `Browser_focus_extension` folder

#### 📱 Kiwi Browser (Android)

Kiwi Browser supports Chrome extensions on Android.

1. Install [Kiwi Browser](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.kiwibrowser.browser) from the Play Store
2. Tap **⋮ menu → Extensions → Load unpacked**
3. Select the `Browser_focus_extension` folder

> **iOS:** Safari on iOS does not support loading custom unpacked extensions.
> This extension cannot be installed on iPhone or iPad without App Store approval.

---

## 🔄 Updating to the Latest Version

```bash
cd Browser_focus_extension
git pull
```

Then go to your browser's extensions page and click the
**reload icon (↺)** on the extension card. No reinstall needed.

---

## 📁 File Structure

```
Browser_focus_extension/
├── manifest.json          ← Extension configuration
├── content.js             ← Injected into every YouTube page
├── hide-distractions.css  ← CSS rules for hiding elements
├── popup.html             ← Settings UI popup
├── popup.css              ← Popup styles
└── popup.js               ← Popup toggle logic
```

---

## 🛡️ Privacy

- No data collection — nothing is tracked or sent anywhere
- No network requests — the extension works fully offline
- Local storage only — your settings stay on your device
- Fully open source — read every line at the link above

---

## 🐛 Found a Bug?

YouTube frequently updates its layout and element names, which can
break selectors. If something stops working, open an issue at:

👉 https://github.com/rejoelbhutia/Browser_focus_extension/issues

